text: Jacques Rosny (25 March 1939 - 18 April 2020) was a French actor and comedian. He was born in Tarbes, France. In 1973, he bought Théâtre de l'Athénée. His best known roles were in The Tenant, Catherine & Co. and L.627. In 1985, he won the Prix du Brigadier. Rosny died on 18 April 2020 of COVID-19 in Nogent- sur-Marne, France, aged 81. ==References== Category:1939 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in France Category:French movie actors Category:French television actors Category:French stage actors Category:French voice actors Category:French comedians Category:Actors from Paris Category:Tarbes Category:People from Hautes-Pyrénées
